    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="350"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d350">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 European War 1939/2428</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The British Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Halifax</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-04">April 4,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Hull</hi>: You will recall that on March 20th I
                    left with you an <hi rend="italic">Aide-Mémoire</hi>
                    <note n="35a" xml:id="d350fn1">Not printed.</note> about the application of the
                    principle of unconditional surrender to minor Axis European States, explaining
                    that a similar approach was being made to the Soviet Government. I now enclose a
                    copy of a telegram from our Ambassador at Moscow<note n="36" xml:id="d350fn2"
                        >Dated March 30, not printed; it gave substance of the communication quoted
                        in memorandum from the Soviet Embassy, March 31, <ref target="#pg_586">p.
                            586</ref>.</note> giving the reply of the Soviet Government.</p>
                <p>Can you now tell me anything more about the United States position?</p>
                <p>Yours very sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Halifax</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
